node.accessibility_caption: Drone photography of a majestic whale shark swimming underneath a local fisherman’s boat in Sulawesi Indonesia rare sighting

node.text:
Dreams do come true ✨

Can you imagine yourself here? 😍

This was a bucket list moment for many years and we couldn’t believe it when we found out that we might be able to see them in a little village called Botubarani just 20 mins from Gorontalo 🥹

We weren’t guaranteed to see them as they come and go as they please, and we were visiting during low season. The government keeps track on how many are spotted each day and they limit the amount of visitors that can go on the water per day 🔎

The pricing for this experience for 2 people is around 250k ($16 USD) which includes being paddled out by a local@in a non- motorized boat, snorkeling equipment, and a grab (like Uber) from the main area in Gorontalo 🤿

The best time to visit Sulawesi is between April - November, if you can try to visit during this time we went in January and the weather was touch and go 🙄
 
📍 Gorontalo, Sulawesi

📌 Save this post for your adventures in Indonesia and follow along for more must visit places 🫶

#sulawesi #gorontalo #wonderfulindonesia #traveladdict #exploreindonesia #whaleshark #whalesharks #exploretheworld #oceanlovers
@octcaizum literally blown away by how amazing they are 🥹 we hope you get to see one soon!!
This’s so wonderful!!😍🥹 you captured very well🔥 One of my list and dreams to visit
@memoriesfromabroad_ thank you! 🙌 the most incredible experience 🥹
This first picture and second video are just mind blowing 🤯😍
@couplesquest_ no way 😍 that is so crazy! I’m sure you will make it reality very soon!🙌
I actually had a dream about swimming by with whale sharks last night 😍 seeing this this morning made me so excited!!! One day 🥹
No way 😱 this is top of our bucket list 😍
@hakuna.matravelers thank you so much 🥰 they are so so beautiful
@two_adventureseekers Sulawesi is such an unreal place 😍 you will love it!
Wow what an amazing shot! We can’t wait to visit Sulawesi soon 😍
wow this is such a special experience 😍
@aprylwanders still not over how incredible this was 🥹🥰
@passportarchives hope that you can make it reality one day somewhere in the world 🥰🫶
Wow 🤩 🥹I am sooooo happy you got to see that fish with your own eyes ❤️ so epic
Wow guys, that’s an unreal experience😮💙
Goodness these shots are too good 😍
You can tell us about this moment for a lifetime. just wow!😍
